# Ingestion Agent Implementation

Build the first agent in the PulseAI pipeline. It reads the 8 mock source files, normalises them into `Signal` records, scores credibility + recency, filters noise (2 throw-in files), and writes `ingestion.json` to `.state/<run_id>/`.

## Proposed Changes

### Schemas

#### [MODIFY] [schemas.py](file:///c:/Users/baisa/Desktop/pulse-ai/agents/ingestion/schemas.py)

Define two pydantic v2 models:

- **`Signal`** — one record per source file. Key fields: `src_id`, `source_type` (Literal), `source_path`, `title`, `timestamp`, `ingested_at`, `credibility` ∈ [0,1], `recency` ∈ [0,1], `region`, `metric`, `content` (dict), `discarded`, `discard_reason`.
- **`IngestionResult`** — aggregation: `run_id`, `seed_region`, `signals` list, `sources_processed`, `sources_discarded`, `discarded_summary`.

