### Tools (pure Python — no LLM)

#### [MODIFY] [tools.py](file:///c:/Users/baisa/Desktop/pulse-ai/agents/ingestion/tools.py)

| Function | Library | Returns |
|---|---|---|
| `parse_pdf(path)` | pypdf | `{text, page_count, creation_date}` |
| `parse_csv(path)` | pandas | `{row_count, columns, head, summary_stats}` |
| `parse_html(path)` | bs4 | `{title, text, byline, date_str}` |
| `parse_json(path)` | stdlib json | `{data: ...}` |
| `parse_jsonl(path)` | stdlib json | `{records: [...], record_count}` |
| `score_credibility(source_type, metadata)` | — | float ∈ [0,1] using the heuristic table from the spec |
| `score_recency(timestamp)` | — | float ∈ [0,1], linear decay over 90 days from `REFERENCE_TODAY` |
| `is_spam(text)` | re | bool — checks for "ACT NOW", "DM me", "limited time", excessive caps, emoji count > 5 |

**Credibility heuristic** (base scores, then adjustments):

| File pattern | Base |
|---|---|
| PDF | 0.85 |
| CSV `pos_ecom` | 0.95 |
| JSON `analytics` | 0.90 |
| JSON `marketing` | 0.85 |
| JSONL `support_tickets` | 0.60 |
| HTML with recognised byline | 0.70 |
| HTML without byline | 0.30 |
| JSON `social_post` with spam | 0.20 |

Adjustments: +0.1 for citations/recognised outlet; −0.3 for spam markers. Clamp to [0, 1].

**Recency**: Uses `REFERENCE_TODAY` (2026-05-17 UTC) from the generator to stay deterministic. Linear decay: age 0 → 1.0, age 90 → 0.0, age >90 → 0.0.

