### Agent

#### [MODIFY] [agent.py](file:///c:/Users/baisa/Desktop/pulse-ai/agents/ingestion/agent.py)

- Define `ingestion_agent = LlmAgent(...)` with model `"gemini-2.5-pro"`, instruction per the spec, and all tools registered.
- Implement `run_ingestion(run_id, seed_region) -> IngestionResult`:
  - Pure Python orchestration (no LLM call).
  - Lists files in `sources/zarapk_regional_v1/<seed_region>/`.
  - Dispatches to the correct parser by extension (`.pdf` → `parse_pdf`, `.csv` → `parse_csv`, `.html` → `parse_html`, `.json` → `parse_json`, `.jsonl` → `parse_jsonl`).
  - Builds a `Signal` per file, assigning `src-1` … `src-N` IDs (sorted by filename for determinism).
  - Scores credibility and recency.
  - Applies discard rule: `credibility < 0.35` OR `is_spam(text)`.
  - Writes result to `.state/<run_id>/ingestion.json`.

> [!NOTE]
> The file-to-parser dispatch uses a fixed mapping by extension. The `title` field is derived from the filename stem. For HTML files, the `<title>` tag is extracted by the parser. The `timestamp` for each source is taken from the parsed metadata where available (PDF creation date, HTML date string, CSV/JSON dates from the data), falling back to file modification time.

